{"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AudioEffectCompressor","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"topicSections":[{"title":"Instance Properties","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AudioEffectCompressor\/attackUs","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AudioEffectCompressor\/gain","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AudioEffectCompressor\/mix","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AudioEffectCompressor\/ratio","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AudioEffectCompressor\/releaseMs","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AudioEffectCompressor\/sidechain","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AudioEffectCompressor\/threshold"]},{"title":"Type Properties","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AudioEffectCompressor\/godotClassName"]}],"kind":"symbol","primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"AudioEffectCompressor","kind":"identifier"}],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Overview","type":"heading","anchor":"overview","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Reduces sounds that exceed a certain threshold level, smooths out the dynamics and increases the overall volume.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Dynamic range compressor reduces the level of the sound when the amplitude goes over a certain threshold in Decibels. One of the main uses of a compressor is to increase the dynamic range by clipping as little as possible (when sound goes over 0dB).","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Compressor has many uses in the mix:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"In the Master bus to compress the whole output (although an ","type":"text"},{"identi